def evaluate_model(model,X,y_true):

  """
  This function takes trained model , X(input) , y_true(true label) as input and 
  evaluates model on different metrics
  """
  th = [0,0.05,0.1,0.15,0.2,0.25,0.3,0.35,0.4,0.45,0.5,0.55,0.6,0.65,0.7,0.75,0.8,0.85,0.9,0.95,1]
  
  pred = model.predict_proba(X)[:,1]
  
  scores = []
  tpr = []
  fpr = []
  

  for i in th:
    pred_labels =[]
    for j in pred:
      if j>=i:
        pred_labels.append(1)
      else:
        pred_labels.append(0)
    scores.append([recall_score(y_true,pred_labels,pos_label=1),precision_score(y_true,pred_labels,pos_label=1)])

    pred_labels = np.array(pred_labels)

    fp = np.sum((pred_labels == 1) & (y_true == 0))
    tp = np.sum((pred_labels == 1) & (y_true == 1))
    fn = np.sum((pred_labels == 0) & (y_true == 1))
    tn = np.sum((pred_labels == 0) & (y_true == 0))
    
    fpr.append(fp / (fp + tn))
    tpr.append(tp / (tp + fn))

    
  f1score = f1_score(y_true, model.predict(X),average = None)
  print("The F1 scores of each class and Macro F1 score are : " , f1score[0] ,f1score[1] , (f1score[0]+f1score[1])/2)

  print(" Accuracy of the model", accuracy_score(y_true, model.predict(X)))
  print(" Sensitivity of the model", recall_score(y_true, model.predict(X),pos_label=1))
  print("Specificity of the model", recall_score(y_true, model.predict(X),pos_label=0))

  #print(confusion_matrix(y_test, model.predict(X_test)))
  cf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_true,model.predict(X))
  print("Confusion Matrix\n",pd.DataFrame(confusion_matrix(y_true,model.predict(X)),\
            columns=["Predicted 0", "Predicted 1"],\
            index=["Actual 0","Actual 1"] ))
  ax = sns.heatmap(cf_matrix, annot=True, cmap='Blues')

  ax.set_title('Seaborn Confusion Matrix with labels\n\n')
  ax.set_xlabel('\nPredicted Values')
  ax.set_ylabel('Actual Values ')

  ## Ticket labels - List must be in alphabetical order
  ax.xaxis.set_ticklabels(['False','True'])
  ax.yaxis.set_ticklabels(['False','True'])

  ## Display the visualization of the Confusion Matrix.
  plt.show()

  

  print("Classification Report\n",classification_report(y_true, model.predict(X)))
  xx = [X[0] for X in scores]
  yy = [Y[1] for Y in scores]
  fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16,12))

  ax1 = fig.add_subplot(311)
  ax1.plot(xx,yy,label = 'AUC PR curve'+str(np.round(auc(xx,yy),3)))

  ax1.set_title("Precision - Recall curve")
  ax1.set_xlabel("Recall")
  ax1.set_ylabel("Precision")
  ax1.legend()

  plt.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=0.2, hspace=0.9)

  ax2 = fig.add_subplot(312)
  ax2.plot(fpr,tpr,label = "Model ROC AUC on test data : "+str(np.round(auc(fpr,tpr),3)))
  ax2.plot([0, 1], ls="--",label='No Skill')
  ax2.set_title("ROC-AUC curve")
  ax2.set_xlabel("FPR")
  ax2.set_ylabel("TPR")
  ax2.legend()
  plt.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=0.2, hspace=0.9)

  features = X_train.columns

  """Rfclf_fea = pd.DataFrame(model.best_estimator_.feature_importances_)
  Rfclf_fea["Feature"] = features 
  Rfclf_fea.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False).head(10)

  g = sns.barplot(0,"Feature",data = Rfclf_fea.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False)[0:10], palette="Pastel1",orient = "h")
  g.set_xlabel("Weight")
  g = g.set_title("Variable Importance")"""

  # get importance
  try:
    importance = model.coef_[0]
  except Exception as e:
    print(e)
  finally:
    importance = model.feature_importances_
  # summarize feature importance
  for i,v in zip(features,importance):
    #pd.DataFrame("Feature":i, "Score": v)
    print('Feature: %s, Score: %.5f' % (i,v))
  #sortd = importance.argsort()
  var_df = pd.DataFrame(model.feature_importances_, columns=['Score'])
  var_df["Feature"] = features
  #var_df.rename(columns = {'0':'Score'}, inplace = True)
  sorted_df = var_df.sort_values(by=["Score"], ascending=True)
  print(sorted_df)
  # plot feature importance
  fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,8))
  
  #ax3.bar(0,"Feature",data = var_df.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False)[0:10])
  ax.barh(sorted_df['Feature'], sorted_df['Score'])
  #ax.set_xlabel("Feature Importance of %s" % model)

  plt.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=0.2, hspace=0.9)

def evaluate_model_Log_svm(model,X,y_true):

  """
  This function takes trained model , X(input) , y_true(true label) as input and 
  evaluates model on different metrics
  """
  th = [0,0.05,0.1,0.15,0.2,0.25,0.3,0.35,0.4,0.45,0.5,0.55,0.6,0.65,0.7,0.75,0.8,0.85,0.9,0.95,1]
  
  pred = model.predict_proba(X)[:,1]
  
  scores = []
  tpr = []
  fpr = []

  for i in th:
    pred_labels =[]
    for j in pred:
      if j>=i:
        pred_labels.append(1)
      else:
        pred_labels.append(0)
    scores.append([recall_score(y_true,pred_labels,pos_label=1),precision_score(y_true,pred_labels,pos_label=1)])

    pred_labels = np.array(pred_labels)

    fp = np.sum((pred_labels == 1) & (y_true == 0))
    tp = np.sum((pred_labels == 1) & (y_true == 1))
    fn = np.sum((pred_labels == 0) & (y_true == 1))
    tn = np.sum((pred_labels == 0) & (y_true == 0))
    
    fpr.append(fp / (fp + tn))
    tpr.append(tp / (tp + fn))
  f1score = f1_score(y_true, model.predict(X),average = None)
  print("The F1 scores of each class and Macro F1 score are : " , f1score[0] ,f1score[1] , (f1score[0]+f1score[1])/2)

  print(" Accuracy of the model", accuracy_score(y_true, model.predict(X)))
  print(" Sensitivity of the model", recall_score(y_true, model.predict(X),pos_label=1))
  print("Specificity of the model", recall_score(y_true, model.predict(X),pos_label=0))

  #print(confusion_matrix(y_test, model.predict(X_test)))
  cf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_true,model.predict(X))
  print("Confusion Matrix\n",pd.DataFrame(confusion_matrix(y_true,model.predict(X)),\
            columns=["Predicted 0", "Predicted 1"],\
            index=["Actual 0","Actual 1"] ))
  ax = sns.heatmap(cf_matrix, annot=True, cmap='Blues')

  ax.set_title('Seaborn Confusion Matrix with labels\n\n')
  ax.set_xlabel('\nPredicted Values')
  ax.set_ylabel('Actual Values ')

  ## Ticket labels - List must be in alphabetical order
  ax.xaxis.set_ticklabels(['False','True'])
  ax.yaxis.set_ticklabels(['False','True'])

  ## Display the visualization of the Confusion Matrix.
  plt.show()



  print("Classification Report\n",classification_report(y_true, model.predict(X)))
  xx = [X[0] for X in scores]
  yy = [Y[1] for Y in scores]
  
  fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16,12))

  ax1 = fig.add_subplot(311)
  ax1.plot(xx,yy,label = 'AUC PR curve'+str(np.round(auc(xx,yy),3)))

  ax1.set_title("Precision - Recall curve")
  ax1.set_xlabel("Recall")
  ax1.set_ylabel("Precision")
  ax1.legend()

  plt.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=0.2, hspace=0.9)

  ax2 = fig.add_subplot(312)
  ax2.plot(fpr,tpr,label = "Model ROC AUC on test data : "+str(np.round(auc(fpr,tpr),3)))
  ax2.plot([0, 1], ls="--",label='No Skill')
  ax2.set_title("ROC-AUC curve")
  ax2.set_xlabel("FPR")
  ax2.set_ylabel("TPR")
  ax2.legend()
  plt.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=0.2, hspace=0.9)

  features = X_train.columns

  """Rfclf_fea = pd.DataFrame(model.best_estimator_.feature_importances_)
  Rfclf_fea["Feature"] = features 
  Rfclf_fea.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False).head(10)

  g = sns.barplot(0,"Feature",data = Rfclf_fea.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False)[0:10], palette="Pastel1",orient = "h")
  g.set_xlabel("Weight")
  g = g.set_title("Variable Importance")"""

  # get importance
  
  importance = model.coef_[0]
  # summarize feature importance
  for i,v in zip(features,importance):
    print('Feature: %s, Score: %.5f' % (i,v))

  var_df = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(features,importance)),columns=['Feature','Score'])
  var_df["Feature"] = features 
  sorted_df = var_df.sort_values(by=['Score'], ascending=False)
  # plot feature importance
  fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,8))
  #ax3.bar(0,"Feature",data = var_df.sort_values(by=0, ascending=False)[0:10])
  ax.barh(sorted_df['Feature'], sorted_df['Score'])

  plt.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=0.2, hspace=0.9)
